XINHUA NEWS APP PRIVACY NOTICE
Thank you for using Xinhua News App (collectively "App" or “we,” “us,” or “our”), which is owned and operated by
		Xinhua
		New Media Culture Communication Co., Ltd, a subsidiary of Xinhua News Agency. Your privacy is very important to us.
		To
		better protect your privacy, we are providing this notice explaining our privacy policy (this Policy), which
		describes
		how we collect, use, share, disclose and process your personal data through your use of Xinhua News App.
INFORMATION WE GATHER
Through Xinhua News App, you can engage in various activities like reading news stories, publishing your opinions,
		joining votes, entering contests, and taking part in quizzes. Your personally identifiable information may be
		collected
		to engage in these activities.
WHAT TYPES OF DATA WE COLLECT?
We collect the following types of data:
Login Information
We collect your profile photo and user ID when you log into our Service with your Facebook,Twitter or WeChat
		account.
		Profile photo in Facebook Twitter or WeChat will be the profile photo of your account in our Service with your
		consent.
		You will not be required to log in or upload any profile photo or have a user ID if you merely use the basic
		functions
		in our Service, such as browsing and searching.
To provide the sharing function, our product integrates Ushare SDK. The SDK will collect the identifiable
		information of
		your device and the public information of your social account you need to share.
User's behavior information
We collect your behaviors information when you use our Service, such as browsing history, search history, comments,
		collections, likes etc.
We collect usage data such as how you use our application, what news you have read and when.
If you are using the Augmented Reality/Virtual Reality (AR/VR) functionality of our application, while biometric
		data
		can be created by picture or video of your visage, we do not collect such data.
Other Information
Identity data such as your gender, age.
Location data such as the city where you are located, the country you reside in.
Technical data such as your IP address, the device you are using. Device information includes device systems,
		device
		manufacturers, device brands, unique device identifier.
OUR LEGITIMAT GROUPS FOR USING PERSONAL INFORMATION
Your consent
Your consent will be necessary in some circumstances under which you will have the right to withdraw that consent
		at any
		time, however, if the consent is withdrawn, we may not be able to continue to provide the service you requested.
Fulfilling a contract
We also process your personal information in order to fulfil a contract we have with you. For example, we would use
		your information to provide you with access to our Service.
Legitimate interests
We may use your information where there are legitimate interests to do so. For example, we will analyze your
		reading
		habits and preferences to recommend more news to you according to your interests, making our Services more
		user-friendly.
		We only rely on legitimate interests if the reason for using your information is fair and lawful. Where we want to
		rely
		on legitimate interests as a legal basis, we will carry out a balancing test between our legitimate interests and
		your
		privacy rights. Our legitimate interests in processing personal information include:
to set up and administer your account, verify your identity, and send important account, subscription and
			service
			information
to deliver and suggest personalized content such as news. We analyze the way you use our Services to make
			suggestions
			to you on content or services that we believe you will also be interested in, and to make our Services more
			user-friendly
for internal research and development purposes and to improve, test and enhance the features and functions of
			our
			Services
to provide you with marketing within the scope permitted by law
to meet our internal and external audit requirements, including our information security obligations
to protect our rights, privacy, safety, networks, systems and property, or those of other persons
for the prevention, detection or investigation of a crime or other breach of law or requirement, loss prevention
			or
			fraud
Compliance with legal obligations
There may be situations where we need to use your information to comply with legal and regulatory obligations or
		defend
		claims.
You are welcome to contact us for further information on the legal grounds that we rely on in relation to any
		specific
		processing of your personal information.
HOW WE USE YOUR DATA AND WHY WE NEED IT?
We process your personal data in accordance with the legal basis under the General Data Protection Regulation
		(GDPR) of
		the European Union and the Cybersecurity Law (CSL) of the People’s Republic of China.
The purposes of our collection and use of the personal data are specified as follows:
To recommend customized news
We will use information about your behavior to make feature tags. Based on such feature tags, we will conduct the
		portrait for a crowd of users to recommend customized news.
To provide personalized service
We will use your device information to provide you with better products or services and personalized information
		display
		service.
