HOW WE STORE YOUR PERSONAL DATA
1. Location of information storage
We will store your personal data collected and generated in the course of operation within the territory of the
		People's
		Republic of China in accordance with applicable laws and regulations.
2. Period of information storage
We will store your data for a period necessary for the purposes set out in this Policy, or when we have a
		legitimate
		reason for doing so. If you ask us to delete your information before the end of the period, we may not be able to do
		so
		due to technical, legal, regulatory or contractual constraints.
If you wish to close your account, we will do this as soon as reasonably possible subject to any applicable terms
		and
		conditions.
HOW WE SHARE YOUR PERSONAL DATA
We will not share your personal data with other companies, organizations or individuals other than the service
		provider of the App, except under following circumstances:
1. Sharing with your consent
We may share your personal data with other companies, organizations or individuals with your explicit consent.
2. Sharing required by law
We may share your personal data with other companies, organizations or individuals required by laws and
		regulations,
		resolving disputes, or responding to requests from administrative or judicial authorities.
3. Sharing with third-party providers
We may share your personal data with third-party providers. For example, your personal data will be shared with
		the
		livestreaming service providers when you use livestreaming service.
The third-party providers with whom your data would be shared are as follows:
		Service providers: we engage service providers to support our business and improve our Service. These service
		providers
		include: the providers for delivery of our digital content and marketing; the provider of livestreaming service;
		business partners with whom we deliver co-branded services, provide content, or to host events, conferences and
		seminars; third parties that help us deliver services or act on our behalf.
SDK: To provide you with one-click sharing service,
		our app has integrate a Ushare SDK supported by Umeng+
		which will collect your device identifiable information
		(such as IMEI/Android ID IDFA,etc.) and the public information of your social account.
		For your information security, we have made data security confidentiality agreements with Umeng+,
		who will strictly abide by our data privacy and security requirements.
		We will not share your personal identifiable information unless authorized by you. For more information,
		please log on to
https://www.umeng.com/policy
to learn about the privacy policy of Umeng+.
To track and collect bugs, our app has integrate a Tencent Bugly SDK which will report errors with your identifiable information (such as IMEI/Android ID IDFA,etc.) to
https://android.bugly.qq.com
We will not share your personal identifiable information unless authorized by you. 
		For more information , please log on to
https://bugly.qq.com/docs/user-guide/instruction-manual-android/?v=1.0.0
4. Sharing with joint-controller
We may share your personal data to joint controllers, who can also determine the purposes and means of the
		processing of
		personal data, such as the advertisers, etc.
We will only share your personal data out of legal, proper, necessary, specific and explicit purposes, and we
		will only
		share necessary information needed to our services. Our partners have no rights to use shared information for
		purposes
		irrelevant to their products and services. Any information that you provide on or to a third-party website or
		service is
		provided directly to the owner of the service and is subject to that party's Privacy Policy. Our Privacy Policy
		does not
		apply to such services and we're not responsible for the content, privacy or security practices and policies of
		those
		services. To protect your information, we recommend that you carefully review the privacy policies of other
		services
		that you access.
CROSS-BORDER DATA TRANSFER
Since our Service is global by nature, it may be necessary for us to transfer your information to our affiliates
		or
		third parties with whom we have a cooperative relationship for our legitimate business purposes, and such
		information
		may be maintained on computers and/or other servers located outside of your state, province, country or other
		governmental jurisdiction in whole or in part where the privacy laws and technology level may not be the same as
		those
		in your jurisdiction.
Please note that the laws vary by jurisdiction, so the privacy laws applicable to the places where your
		information is
		transferred or stored, used, or processed, may be different from the privacy laws of the jurisdiction you reside
		in.
The collected information may be stored in the People's Republic of China. By choosing to visit the Service or
		provide
		information to us, you agree that any dispute over privacy or the terms contained in this Privacy Policy will be
		governed by the laws of China and the adjudication of any disputes arising in connection with us or our Service
		will be
		in accordance with the Terms of Use on the App. When we transfer your information globally, we guarantee that your
		information will be transferred securely and lawfully. We have taken appropriate safeguards to ensure that your
		personal
		information will be protected in accordance with this Policy and we hereby ensure that any third party acting as
		our
		agent would do the same.
Users should direct any questions, concerns or complaints regarding the processing of personal information at:
		XinhuaNews_Support@xhsxmt.com. We will duly handle your questions. However, please note that our Service may not
		be
		available to you if you reject international information transfer.
DATA SECURITY
We have adopted proper security measures in compliance with industry standards to protect the privacy and
		security of
		your personal data, to prevent personal data from being accessed without permission, disclosed, used, edited,
		damaged or
		lost. For example, we use Security Sockets Layer (SSL) to secure information transfers between your browsers and
		servers; we use HTTPS when you browse the App; we use encryption technologies to improve security of personal
		data; we
		use reliable protection systems to prevent attacks; we deploy an access control system to ensure that only
		authorized
		person can access to personal data; and we will train our employees on privacy protection as well as how to handle
		and
		manage your data appropriately.
If your personal data breaches, we will inform you according to relevant laws and regulations of the basic
		situation,
		possible influence, our remedial solutions taken or will be taken, and offer self-protection or self-prevention
		suggestions to you and make necessary remedial measures. We will communicate with you by e-mail, mail, phone calls
		and/or alerts. If we cannot reach to all affected individuals, we will publish announcements in proper and
		effective
		ways.
YOUR RIGHTS
You have the rights under applicable laws to have access to your personal data and to ask us to rectify, erase
		and
		restrict the use of your personal data. You also have the rights to object to your personal data being used, to
		ask for
		the transfer of personal data you have made available to us and to withdraw consent to the use of your personal
		data.
		You may find further information on how to exercise your rights set out underneath.
We honor your rights under applicable data protection laws. You have following rights under laws of the People's
		Republic of China, and may have similar rights under the laws of other countries.
1. Right to access
You have the right to make a written request for details of your personal data and a copy of that personal data.
2. Right to rectification
You have the right to have inaccurate information about you corrected or removed.
3. Right to erasure
You have the right to have certain personal data about you erased.
4. Right to restriction of processing
You have the right to request that your personal data would only be used for restricted purposes.
5. Right to object
You have the right to object to our processing of your personal data based on the performance of a task carried
		out in
		the public interest or we have let you know the processing is necessary for our or a third party's legitimate
		interests.
6. Right to data portability
You have the right to ask for the personal data you have made available to us to be transferred to you or a third
		party
		in machine-readable format.
7. Right to withdraw consent
You have the right to withdraw any consent you previously gave us. If you withdraw your consent, this will not
		affect
		the lawfulness of our use of your personal data prior to the withdrawal of your consent.
8. Right to compliant
You may make a complaint to the supervisory authority.
These rights are not absolute and they do not always apply in all cases.
In response to a request, we will ask you to verify your identity if we need to, and to provide information that
		helps
		us to understand your request better. If we do not comply with your request, whether in whole or in part, we will
		explain why.
To exercises any of these rights please contact us at XinhuaNews_Support@xhsxmt.com with details of your request.
		If you
		have any questions about these rights, you may also contact us at the above e-mail.
UPDATES TO THIS POLICY
Our Privacy Policy may be amended from time to time. Any such changes will be posted on our main Privacy Policy
		page. If
		we make a significant or material change in the way we use your personal data, the change will be posted thirty
		(30)
		days prior to taking effect and registered users will be notified via e-mail. We employ measures designed to
		protect the
		security of your personal identifying information.
